<br>
Just thought I would post something that I find interesting.  <br>
<br>
While I do not know &quot;all&quot; of the high lvl clerics on the server I would like to think I know most of them.<br>
<br>
Muzzle, Hwoarang, Kaeyne, Dorr, Lyfane, etc....<br>
<br>
One thing seems to be fairly apparant....<br>
<br>
None of us ever charged for res's.<br>
<br>
I think this is a mind set thing, if you play a cleric because you truly &quot;want to help&quot; then you will take the cleric to the top because you honestly can't think of a class that can help more.<br>
<br>
If you play for money or loot then you will burn out fairly quickly in the 40s.  The Cleric is never in a &quot;Glory&quot; position and quite frankly our equipment doesn't get all that exciting.  If your goal isn't to help others have fun purely for the enjoyment you get from seeing others have fun, then perhaps you have picked the wrong class...<br>
<br>
If you are a mid lvl cleric (39-49) and you are charging for res's (I know there are always special circumstances, I think you know what I mean) then perhaps you should re-look at your class selection.  The 50+ levels are not easy, exp moves very very slow and it can take a lot of time to get a group started.  Very few places (other then Karnors) to just walk in and get a pick up group.  After about 55 then Karnors starts to turn green and pick up groups become a thing of the past...<br>
<br>
Just a thought,<br>
<br>
Camdar Sol'Dara<br>
56 Templar<br>
