<br>
Ahh ... the thorny issues of rezzes, the greatest blessing AND the greatest curse of every cleric's life.<br>
<br>
Deciding whether to rez someone based on whatever criteria is one thing, and not the subject of this thread (been done to death elsewere); however, suffice to say I regularly have to refuse to rez someone for a variety of reasons.<br>
<br>
However, if I have agreed to rez someone, then, as is usual for all decisions for Felishanna, the decision regarding taking money for rezzes is based on her own (not anyone elses) roleplayed view of Tunare's will, and in this case it happens to concur with the commonly held non-roleplaying view that by and large the acceptance of money for rezzes is not really what it is all about. Felishanna looks at it like this: Tunare has blessed her with this power for a purpose, and that purpose was not to make money, but help all that is good in the land of Norrath.<br>
<br>
Consequently, I have *never* asked for payment of any kind, nor has the offer of payment ever made me decide to give a rez where otherwise I would not have. I have, rarely, accepted a donation offered, in cases where I've had to put myself to some considerable trouble to do the rez (eg run a zone, get a TP and then run another zone to get to a corpse), but it has been neither expected nor required (after all, I could quite reasonably have said 'no', couldn't I?). I have also, rarely, accepted a donation where I have kept a group of others waiting due to doing the rez, and then promptly split the donation with the group who were made to so wait. Perhaps I have accepted a donation a few other times, like half a dozen times ever. But on 95%+ of occasions, I have refused any offered donation (the offer itself is an act of appreciation, and is always noted as a good mark for the person concerned, but its acceptance is not required).<br>
<br>
However, I am not quick to judge others who choose to accept donations for rezzes. As with most things, it is a matter of 'each to their own'. <br>
<br>
Felishanna Secretlight<br>
Cleric of Tunare of 55 Seasons.<br>
Mithril Web (www.mithrilweb.com)<br>
Lanys T'Vyl<br>
